1
00:01:49,500 --> 00:01:52,041
[FARIA] Madams and Monsieurs,
good evening.

2
00:01:52,125 --> 00:01:54,333
The girl sleeping in the
house of the poisoner

3
00:01:54,416 --> 00:01:57,208
was saved thanks to the
pure souls of the young men

4
00:01:57,291 --> 00:02:00,416
who were her friends
and confidants

5
00:02:00,500 --> 00:02:03,375
However, the next
misfortune silently creeps up

6
00:02:03,458 --> 00:02:06,000
and suddenly appears before us.

7
00:02:06,083 --> 00:02:08,208
Indeed, just like
that single letter that

8
00:02:08,291 --> 00:02:11,666
was delivered to
an innocent soul.

9
00:02:20,041 --> 00:02:34,875
♪ piano music ♪

10
00:02:34,958 --> 00:02:36,416
Excuse me?

11
00:02:36,500 --> 00:02:37,833
What did you say?

12
00:02:37,916 --> 00:02:40,541
Father! Did I hear you right?

13
00:02:40,625 --> 00:02:41,750
Yes.

14
00:02:41,833 --> 00:02:43,791
I've called off your
engagement to Albert...

15
00:02:45,166 --> 00:02:47,250
That's all there
is to it. All right?

16
00:02:47,333 --> 00:02:48,958
What's the meaning of this?

17
00:02:49,041 --> 00:02:50,791
Why, father?!

18
00:02:50,875 --> 00:02:53,125
I've been hearing
some unsavory rumors

19
00:02:53,208 --> 00:02:55,000
regarding the Morcerfs.

20
00:02:55,083 --> 00:02:58,083
But that doesn't mean you--
I can't believe this!

21
00:02:58,166 --> 00:02:59,500
I don't get it.

22
00:02:59,583 --> 00:03:01,166
You never wanted to marry him.

23
00:03:01,250 --> 00:03:05,708
In fact, if I recall, you were
very upset about it at first.

24
00:03:05,791 --> 00:03:07,541
It seems that you
don't understand much

25
00:03:07,625 --> 00:03:08,958
about anything, do you?

26
00:03:09,041 --> 00:03:11,250
So stop treating my
life like it was one of

27
00:03:11,333 --> 00:03:13,708
your own personal
stocks or bonds!

28
00:03:14,625 --> 00:03:16,333
Here's a quick lesson for you.

29
00:03:16,416 --> 00:03:18,833
In this world, there's
only two kinds of people,

30
00:03:18,916 --> 00:03:20,500
winners and losers.

31
00:03:20,583 --> 00:03:22,583
Eugenie.

32
00:03:22,666 --> 00:03:25,750
I'm only thinking of
what's best for you.

33
00:03:25,833 --> 00:03:27,000
Liar.

34
00:03:27,083 --> 00:03:29,375
It's what's best for YOU!

35
00:03:36,833 --> 00:03:38,916
Damn it, Mondego...

36
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:40,875
You really blew it.

37
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:44,791
Sorry, but I plan to
make it through this.

38
00:03:46,791 --> 00:03:48,708
I must say, it's hard to believe

39
00:03:48,791 --> 00:03:51,208
you're the Mondego
I used to know.

40
00:03:51,291 --> 00:03:53,250
You've done well for yourself.

41
00:03:53,333 --> 00:03:56,625
Really. And how
do you know that?

42
00:03:58,583 --> 00:04:02,666
A certain gentleman I know,
told me a lot about you.

43
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:04,166
Who was it?! Tell me!!

44
00:04:09,541 --> 00:04:10,875
I can't tell you...

45
00:04:10,958 --> 00:04:13,375
But that's not important.

46
00:04:14,416 --> 00:04:17,291
What do you want? How much?

47
00:04:19,958 --> 00:04:22,416
Gimme everything!
All you've got!

48
00:04:22,500 --> 00:04:23,708
If you wanna keep
me from talking,

49
00:04:23,791 --> 00:04:26,500
stuff my mouth with gold!

50
00:04:33,333 --> 00:04:36,083
It's an honor to see
you again, Mademoiselle.

51
00:04:37,208 --> 00:04:39,250
Marquis Cavalcanti?

52
00:04:39,333 --> 00:04:41,208
You here on business?

53
00:04:41,291 --> 00:04:43,833
Yes, I have a meeting
with your father.

54
00:04:43,916 --> 00:04:47,250
What, more financial dealings?

55
00:04:47,333 --> 00:04:48,875
I was hoping that
I could perhaps help you

56
00:04:48,958 --> 00:04:50,791
in some way or another.

57
00:04:54,083 --> 00:04:58,958
Whatever causes you sorrow,
I wish to make it go away.

58
00:04:59,666 --> 00:05:03,208
You have absolutely no
reason to do that for me.

59
00:05:04,833 --> 00:05:08,583
Does a man need a
reason to love a woman?

60
00:05:11,541 --> 00:05:13,750
No! Let go of me!

61
00:05:14,666 --> 00:05:16,250
Touch me and I'll scream!

62
00:05:16,333 --> 00:05:19,958
You're acquainted with the Count
of Monte Cristo, aren't you?

63
00:05:20,875 --> 00:05:23,583
The gossip
regarding the Morcerfs...

64
00:05:23,666 --> 00:05:27,083
...was apparently leaked
by the Count himself.

65
00:05:27,875 --> 00:05:29,000
What are you saying?

66
00:05:29,083 --> 00:05:30,250
Of course...

67
00:05:30,333 --> 00:05:32,791
I find it unlikely that
the Count's information

68
00:05:32,875 --> 00:05:34,625
would be incorrect.

69
00:05:34,708 --> 00:05:35,625
I don't understand.

70
00:05:35,708 --> 00:05:37,958
Why are you telling me this?

71
00:05:39,291 --> 00:05:42,250
The thought of seeing
sadness on your face...

72
00:05:42,333 --> 00:05:43,875
...is painful.

73
00:05:44,416 --> 00:05:45,666
Cut it out.

74
00:05:45,750 --> 00:05:48,125
There's no reason for you
to be in love with me.

75
00:05:54,750 --> 00:05:58,083
Why would the Count of Monte
Cristo do such a thing...?

76
00:06:06,375 --> 00:06:07,416
I wonder what she thinks

77
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:09,875
about the engagement
being called off?

78
00:06:11,333 --> 00:06:13,458
[PEPPO] Why don't
you just ask the girl?

79
00:06:15,375 --> 00:06:21,083
No, this problem might be a lot
bigger than just the two of us.

80
00:06:21,166 --> 00:06:23,666
Albert you're...

81
00:06:23,750 --> 00:06:26,041
...serious about her.

82
00:06:27,125 --> 00:06:29,166
I guess it's true that
you don't realize

83
00:06:29,250 --> 00:06:32,958
how important something
is until you lose it.

84
00:06:35,416 --> 00:06:36,583
My goodness.

85
00:06:36,666 --> 00:06:39,375
Now this is what
I call amazing...

86
00:06:39,458 --> 00:06:41,833
This is your daughter's
big night, after all.

87
00:06:41,916 --> 00:06:43,916
Money is no object.

88
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:46,208
My daughter is a lucky girl.

89
00:06:46,291 --> 00:06:47,958
Let's face it, she never
would have been able

90
00:06:48,041 --> 00:06:51,000
to sell out the opera house
simply on her own merits.

91
00:06:51,083 --> 00:06:52,166
This would never have happened

92
00:06:52,250 --> 00:06:54,791
without your gracious
support Monsieur.

93
00:06:56,291 --> 00:06:57,333
So...

94
00:06:57,416 --> 00:06:59,166
...are you willing to
go along with this?

95
00:06:59,250 --> 00:07:02,541
Breaking your
engagement to Albert?

96
00:07:02,625 --> 00:07:03,958
It's hardly breaking it off.

97
00:07:04,041 --> 00:07:06,875
I mean, nothing had
even started between us.

98
00:07:06,958 --> 00:07:09,583
Maybe, but... the two of you
were engaged, after all.

99
00:07:09,666 --> 00:07:11,583
This was decided by...

100
00:07:11,666 --> 00:07:13,875
...both our families.

101
00:07:14,750 --> 00:07:15,666
Yeah?

102
00:07:15,750 --> 00:07:17,916
Then why do you
seem so hurt by it?

103
00:07:19,208 --> 00:07:20,583
Who is he?

104
00:07:20,666 --> 00:07:22,708
Who's this
Count of Monte Cristo?

105
00:07:22,791 --> 00:07:25,666
Why are you asking?
Did he do something?

106
00:07:25,750 --> 00:07:27,583
He's manipulating things.

107
00:07:27,666 --> 00:07:29,750
I'm sure he was the
source of the bad rumors

108
00:07:29,833 --> 00:07:32,875
about Albert's family
that my father's been hearing.

109
00:07:32,958 --> 00:07:34,833
Bad rumors?

110
00:07:34,916 --> 00:07:38,708
When it comes to that political
gossip, I really don't care...

111
00:07:38,791 --> 00:07:42,541
...but Albert hasn't been the
same since he met the Count.

112
00:07:43,500 --> 00:07:45,875
Hey Franz don't
you miss the old days?

113
00:07:45,958 --> 00:07:47,583
The three of us would
run around the meadow,

114
00:07:47,666 --> 00:07:50,250
not even noticing when
the sun went down.

115
00:07:54,791 --> 00:07:56,125
When did it start?

116
00:07:56,208 --> 00:07:59,583
When did we start being so
awkward around each other,

117
00:07:59,666 --> 00:08:02,333
not even able to
hold hands anymore?

118
00:08:05,083 --> 00:08:08,875
When you two were on Luna,
what happened to you?

119
00:08:08,958 --> 00:08:10,125
Neither one of you...

120
00:08:10,208 --> 00:08:12,666
...has been the
same since that trip.

121
00:08:21,541 --> 00:08:22,958
No, we haven't.

122
00:08:23,041 --> 00:08:24,166
And what about Albert?

123
00:08:24,250 --> 00:08:26,916
What does he think about
what's been happening?

124
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:29,375
I haven't heard
from him at all.

125
00:08:29,458 --> 00:08:31,708
Has he said
anything to you?

126
00:08:31,791 --> 00:08:34,541
Aren't you...
best friends with him?

127
00:08:34,625 --> 00:08:37,166
Best friends, right...

128
00:08:50,208 --> 00:08:52,541
Franz, is something wrong?

129
00:08:52,625 --> 00:08:54,208
I'm sorry.

130
00:08:54,291 --> 00:08:57,416
I don't really understand
him these days, either.

131
00:08:57,500 --> 00:08:58,500
Hey wait a minute.

132
00:08:58,583 --> 00:09:01,083
Did something happen?

133
00:09:01,166 --> 00:09:02,375
We got into a fight.

134
00:09:02,458 --> 00:09:04,041
Huh?

135
00:09:04,125 --> 00:09:08,125
Albert shouldn't associate
with the Count anymore...

136
00:09:11,458 --> 00:09:13,666
Thanks a lot,
Franz for lending an ear.

137
00:09:13,750 --> 00:09:16,166
Sorry I couldn't
be more helpful.

138
00:09:16,250 --> 00:09:17,666
Still...

139
00:09:17,750 --> 00:09:19,000
What?

140
00:09:19,083 --> 00:09:20,083
I'm relieved.

141
00:09:20,166 --> 00:09:21,250
Huh?

142
00:09:21,333 --> 00:09:22,541
Well...

143
00:09:22,625 --> 00:09:24,416
Whatever you might say
when it comes to Albert

144
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:27,375
it looks like the truth is
that you really do care.

145
00:09:28,458 --> 00:09:31,291
Is it that obvious?

146
00:09:31,375 --> 00:09:34,333
No one can hide when
they're pining away

147
00:09:34,416 --> 00:09:35,958
for someone they love.

148
00:09:38,458 --> 00:09:39,583
I was thinking.

149
00:09:39,666 --> 00:09:41,291
Maybe the reason your
piano performance

150
00:09:41,375 --> 00:09:43,083
that night at
Auteuil was great...

151
00:09:43,166 --> 00:09:46,416
...was because you were
really playing it for Albert.

152
00:09:47,500 --> 00:09:48,541
No way...

153
00:09:48,625 --> 00:09:49,875
But your feelings,

154
00:09:49,958 --> 00:09:52,583
always manifest
themselves in your art.

155
00:09:52,666 --> 00:09:54,125
Aren't I right?

156
00:10:17,291 --> 00:10:19,625
Yeah, he wouldn't be here...

157
00:10:22,375 --> 00:10:25,666
After all, he and
I are still fighting...

158
00:10:35,583 --> 00:10:38,875
Yeah, he wouldn't be here...

159
00:10:51,625 --> 00:10:53,291
What's keeping her?

160
00:10:53,375 --> 00:10:55,291
Isn't Eugenie
ready yet?!

161
00:10:55,375 --> 00:10:58,166
She's still
preparing Monseiur.

162
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:01,791
Mademoiselle , are you
sure you're feeling all right?

163
00:11:01,875 --> 00:11:03,375
I'm fine.

164
00:11:03,458 --> 00:11:07,291
Tonights performance is the one
I've dreamt of my whole life.

165
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:14,125
[MERCEDES] It's the
strangest thing.

166
00:11:14,208 --> 00:11:17,083
Unlike the way it is
outside of the city walls,

167
00:11:17,166 --> 00:11:21,291
the grapevines always bear
fruit no matter the season.

168
00:11:22,250 --> 00:11:24,458
What is it?

169
00:11:25,666 --> 00:11:28,416
Albert, dear...

170
00:11:28,875 --> 00:11:32,708
...you should always listen
to your inner feelings.

171
00:11:32,791 --> 00:11:34,875
You can't fool
yourself into feeling

172
00:11:34,958 --> 00:11:37,750
a certain way about somebody.

173
00:11:40,125 --> 00:11:44,583
Yeah, well, have you always
been true to yourself, Mother?

174
00:11:46,916 --> 00:11:48,416
This is Paris.

175
00:11:48,500 --> 00:11:50,083
Perhaps it truly
is a paradise

176
00:11:50,166 --> 00:11:53,083
where you can find
whatever your heart desires.

177
00:11:54,416 --> 00:11:57,208
But then again,
if you lose your courage,

178
00:11:57,291 --> 00:12:00,250
you'll simply be swept
along with the currents.

179
00:12:18,750 --> 00:12:21,416
You're not going to
show up... are you Albert?

180
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:29,666
Are you looking
for someone?

181
00:12:29,750 --> 00:12:30,958
Lucien!

182
00:12:32,416 --> 00:12:33,250
I get it.

183
00:12:33,333 --> 00:12:35,916
Mother invited you, didn't she?

184
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:37,500
She's very kind.

185
00:12:37,583 --> 00:12:41,333
I've decided to dedicate my
performance tonight to lovers.

186
00:12:41,416 --> 00:12:43,458
I hope that you and
Mother will enjoy it.

187
00:12:43,541 --> 00:12:44,583
No.

188
00:12:44,666 --> 00:12:46,833
This evening, you
should play for yourself

189
00:12:46,916 --> 00:12:48,708
and for the person
that you love.

190
00:12:48,791 --> 00:12:51,583
Pianists are allowed
to do that, you know.

191
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:54,875
That's easy for
you to say...

192
00:12:56,500 --> 00:12:58,583
Right.

193
00:13:08,166 --> 00:13:09,625
Ah, Albert.

194
00:13:09,708 --> 00:13:11,166
I'm sorry, but
the hall is filled

195
00:13:11,250 --> 00:13:13,833
to capacity with invited guests.

196
00:13:13,916 --> 00:13:16,083
But Monsieur,
I have an invitation.

197
00:13:16,166 --> 00:13:17,708
Eugenie gave it to me.

198
00:13:17,791 --> 00:13:18,875
Hmph!

199
00:13:18,958 --> 00:13:20,458
What's done is done.

200
00:13:20,541 --> 00:13:23,000
Let's just pretend
it never happened.

201
00:13:23,083 --> 00:13:26,208
But Barron, I was invited
to come by Eugenie!

202
00:13:26,291 --> 00:13:27,916
You can not turn me away!

203
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:29,208
You have no right!

204
00:13:29,291 --> 00:13:31,708
Well, well. Did you get
that firey hot temper

205
00:13:31,791 --> 00:13:33,583
of yours from your father?

206
00:13:33,666 --> 00:13:35,708
This has nothing
to do with my father!

207
00:13:35,791 --> 00:13:37,666
I'm coming in!

208
00:13:40,541 --> 00:13:43,291
And just how are you
going to accomplish that?

209
00:13:43,375 --> 00:13:44,333
No power...

210
00:13:44,416 --> 00:13:46,375
No money...

211
00:13:46,458 --> 00:13:48,458
You're nothing
but a spoiled brat!

212
00:13:48,541 --> 00:13:50,500
Shut up!

213
00:13:50,583 --> 00:13:52,916
I may be a brat
but I-l-- Damn it!

214
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:54,000
Let me go!

215
00:13:54,083 --> 00:13:55,333
What's this commotion?

216
00:13:55,416 --> 00:13:56,916
It's quite disturbing.

217
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:59,083
Oh, you were invited, too?

218
00:13:59,166 --> 00:14:02,416
Yes, by Madame.

219
00:14:03,833 --> 00:14:07,083
My wife seems to be feeling
a little out of sorts tonight.

220
00:14:07,166 --> 00:14:10,208
You wouldn't mind keeping her
company for me, would you?

221
00:14:10,291 --> 00:14:12,125
I'm sorry,...

222
00:14:12,208 --> 00:14:14,250
...but I'm not
in the mood today.

223
00:14:14,333 --> 00:14:16,166
Please excuse me.

224
00:14:16,250 --> 00:14:17,166
[ALBERT]
Lucien, cut it out!

225
00:14:17,250 --> 00:14:20,375
I-I have to get in there!

226
00:14:20,458 --> 00:14:21,041
Listen to me!

227
00:14:21,125 --> 00:14:21,875
Albert, stop!

228
00:14:21,958 --> 00:14:23,125
Use your head!

229
00:14:23,208 --> 00:14:25,208
You'll never get in
through the front door.

230
00:14:26,500 --> 00:14:27,708
Damn it!

231
00:14:27,791 --> 00:14:30,166
Look, I don't owe you
any favors or anything,

232
00:14:30,250 --> 00:14:31,625
but I've been doing
some things lately

233
00:14:31,708 --> 00:14:33,625
that have been hurting Eugenie.

234
00:14:34,625 --> 00:14:37,875
Are... Are you really sleeping
with Eugenie's mother?

235
00:14:37,958 --> 00:14:39,583
It's all part of my job.

236
00:14:39,666 --> 00:14:42,083
You'll never understand
it so don't even try.

237
00:14:42,166 --> 00:14:43,708
You don't have any need to.

238
00:14:43,791 --> 00:14:47,666
Anyway, you go in
and be there for her.

239
00:14:47,750 --> 00:14:49,833
You love Eugenie, don't you?

240
00:14:49,916 --> 00:14:52,125
[buzz]

241
00:14:52,208 --> 00:14:54,000
Let's go.

242
