256
00:17:27,125 --> 00:17:29,166
Albert? Is that...

257
00:17:29,250 --> 00:17:30,666
...you?

258
00:17:33,125 --> 00:17:34,916
You're a little late,
don't you think?!

259
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:36,791
I was right here
the whole time.

260
00:17:38,375 --> 00:17:41,166
I had a little
trouble getting in.

261
00:17:41,250 --> 00:17:43,500
You don't mean
my father, do you?

262
00:17:44,583 --> 00:17:45,583
It's all right,

263
00:17:45,666 --> 00:17:47,666
I heard you
play just fine.

264
00:17:47,750 --> 00:17:49,375
It was wonderful.

265
00:17:51,041 --> 00:17:52,833
You were radiant.

266
00:17:52,916 --> 00:17:55,041
My heart was racing!

267
00:17:56,208 --> 00:17:57,208
Idiot.

268
00:17:57,291 --> 00:17:59,208
If I'd known
you were here,

269
00:17:59,291 --> 00:18:01,916
I would've been able
to play even better.

270
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:04,291
I'd have played for you.

271
00:18:05,125 --> 00:18:06,916
Eugenie...

272
00:18:19,250 --> 00:18:20,416
I'm sorry.

273
00:18:20,500 --> 00:18:24,583
I-I know that I'm not
your fiance anymore but...

274
00:18:24,666 --> 00:18:25,750
That doesn't matter.

275
00:18:25,833 --> 00:18:27,708
I don't care.

276
00:18:29,083 --> 00:18:30,500
Oh!

277
00:18:30,583 --> 00:18:31,916
Here.

278
00:18:33,291 --> 00:18:34,125
What?

279
00:18:34,208 --> 00:18:35,625
You like these, don't you?

280
00:18:35,708 --> 00:18:38,041
Well, sure, but Albert...

281
00:18:38,125 --> 00:18:41,000
...you're supposed to bring
me a big bouquet of flowers.

282
00:18:41,083 --> 00:18:42,041
Oh, right.

283
00:18:42,125 --> 00:18:44,416
I guess flowers
would've been better.

284
00:18:46,208 --> 00:18:47,875
You are such a dork.

285
00:18:47,958 --> 00:18:51,166
It's like when we were kids

286
00:18:52,708 --> 00:18:56,333
In the meadow, I wanted
you to pick flowers for me...

287
00:18:56,416 --> 00:19:00,000
...but you would always
bring me berries instead.

288
00:19:01,041 --> 00:19:04,500
Even so, They were
always delicious.

289
00:19:16,458 --> 00:19:18,791
Mademoiselle Eugenie!

290
00:19:18,875 --> 00:19:21,750
You know it won't do to
keep your audience waiting.

291
00:19:21,833 --> 00:19:22,666
You!

292
00:19:22,750 --> 00:19:24,625
No! Wait, Albert!

293
00:19:24,708 --> 00:19:27,250
Listen to one more piece.

294
00:19:27,333 --> 00:19:29,000
For you...

295
00:19:29,083 --> 00:19:31,958
I'm gonna be playing
it just for you.

296
00:19:37,041 --> 00:19:48,333
♪ piano music ♪

297
00:19:48,416 --> 00:19:52,250
Oh well, It seems like
there's no place for you here.

298
00:19:52,333 --> 00:19:54,666
I wouldn't be so sure.

299
00:19:57,458 --> 00:20:06,125
[AUDIENCE applause]

300
00:20:06,208 --> 00:20:07,666
Madams and Messieurs!

301
00:20:07,750 --> 00:20:11,625
The star of the evening
Mademoiselle Eugenie!

302
00:20:13,541 --> 00:20:14,666
What do you
think you're doing?!

303
00:20:14,750 --> 00:20:17,583
This is supposed
to be my performance!

304
00:20:17,666 --> 00:20:21,875
It is. A performance
that I arranged.

305
00:20:21,958 --> 00:20:23,833
Huh?

306
00:20:23,916 --> 00:20:24,666
Hey!

307
00:20:24,750 --> 00:20:27,458
You don't know when to quit!

308
00:20:27,541 --> 00:20:28,750
My daughter is now on the road

309
00:20:28,833 --> 00:20:30,958
to a brighter future
than she'd have with you!

310
00:20:31,041 --> 00:20:33,500
You're not going
to ruin it for her!

311
00:20:33,583 --> 00:20:35,666
You don't have
any right to be here!

312
00:20:35,750 --> 00:20:37,041
All the seats for
tonight's performance

313
00:20:37,125 --> 00:20:39,875
were bought by the
Marquis Cavalcanti!

314
00:20:39,958 --> 00:20:42,333
You've lost, so go away!

315
00:20:58,541 --> 00:21:00,375
Count...

316
00:21:02,208 --> 00:21:04,791
Albert, whatever
is the matter?

317
00:21:04,875 --> 00:21:08,958
I'm afraid that you're not
looking very well at all.

318
00:21:13,458 --> 00:21:15,041
Count!

319
00:21:15,125 --> 00:21:16,291
Albert?

320
00:21:16,375 --> 00:21:19,541
I'm... so frustrated...

321
00:21:19,625 --> 00:21:25,958
At how weak and
pathetic I really am...

322
00:21:30,541 --> 00:21:33,208
Count of Monte Cristo!

323
00:21:33,291 --> 00:21:35,625
You are suspected
of criminal activity.

324
00:21:35,708 --> 00:21:37,833
I will have to ask you to
come with me to the station

325
00:21:37,916 --> 00:21:40,875
as the prime suspect in
the poisoning of Valois!

326
00:21:40,958 --> 00:21:43,000
Monsieur Villefort...

327
00:23:28,625 --> 00:23:31,166
[ALBERT] Villefort's
investigation is relentless.

328
00:23:31,250 --> 00:23:32,041
Why?

329
00:23:32,125 --> 00:23:33,208
When I go to visit the Count,

330
00:23:33,291 --> 00:23:35,083
I speak with Haidee
for the first time.

331
00:23:35,166 --> 00:23:37,458
Next Gankutsuou,
The Count of Monte Cristo,

332
00:23:37,541 --> 00:23:39,833
Act 13: "Hadee".

333
00:23:39,916 --> 00:23:41,458
Bide your time,
and hold out hope!

